this code only animates when toast disappears. How to make it animate appear as well?
To ensure that the toast view animates both when it appears and disappears, you need to use the `.transition` modifier effectively. The `.opacity` transition only animates the opacity, but you can combine it with other transitions or use a custom transition to achieve the desired effect.

Here's an updated version of your code that uses a combined transition for both appearing and disappearing animations:

```swift
struct ErrorToastModifier: ViewModifier {

  @StateObject private var errorToastPresenter = ErrorToastController()

  func body(content: Content) -> some View {
    ZStack {
      content

      if let message = errorToastPresenter.message {
        toastView(text: message.text)
          .task {
            await dismissToast(after: message.duration)
          }
          .zIndex(2)
          .animation(.default, value: errorToastPresenter.message)
          .transition(.asymmetric(insertion: .opacity.combined(with: .move(edge: .top)), removal: .opacity))
      }
    }
  }
}
```

In this code, the `.transition(.asymmetric(insertion: .opacity.combined(with: .move(edge: .top)), removal: .opacity))` line specifies that the toast view should use a combined transition when it appears (insertion) and a simple opacity transition when it disappears (removal). The `.move(edge: .top)` transition makes the toast slide in from the top, and the `.opacity` transition handles the fade effect.

Feel free to adjust the transitions to match your desired animation effects.
